`Cannot decide shape for the following arguments...`. What are the input args that the error message suggests you consider providing shapes for?

What is `x2` in your script?

@reminisce No, those are not mistakes :p The concat dim was deliberately dim=1 and *not* dim=0. This simplified example actually followed from a use case myself and colleagues had where concat was on a second dimension (has to do with mixture models).

The broadcast_axis was also deliberately sized to zero so that it can be inferred to match the batch dimension. (In actual practice x would be something more like a data arg and y a tunable variable/weight, but I don't think it's important to describe the specific reasoning we ran into this problem). size=0 in this way is entirely valid when the operations support the backward shape inference, as in shown in the last code block I posted (that eschews the expand_dims) which also has size=0 in the broadcast and which works fine.

The problem seems to be with expand_dims. As piiswrong said, it sounds like the issue is that expand_dims doesn't do the backward shape inference. Since I'm not up to speed on the backend side of mxnet, it's not something I can fix myself soon. If someone else sees this and can tackle this issue before me though, that would be great.

