If you compile your program on Linux, you can use gdb to view the core file. I test following program, it works fine and the program gives correct results(6, 4). (mxnet build from master branch)

I save NDArray in python and load it back using C++. Maybe you can check whether the two versions of libmxnet.so (write in python and read in cpp) are compatible if they are not the same.

```python
import mxnet as mx

x = mx.nd.zeros((2,3))
y = mx.nd.ones((1,4))
mx.nd.save('my_list', [x,y])
mx.nd.save('my_dict', {'x':x, 'y':y})
l = mx.nd.load('my_list')
d = mx.nd.load('my_dict')

print l[0].shape
```

